This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for hand pose estimation, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a recurrent neural network (RNN) for capturing the spatial dependencies between adjacent joints, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and fully-connected layers, which are common machine learning techniques and could place the paper in the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of depth maps as input, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
